        <mxCell id="OebSlb7G5yYJ-OwYx5fL-4" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;ISSUE:&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;Redis is great for likes, but view count happens to be an exponentially higher rate.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;Writing every single view to a DB or cache overwhelm the system.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;SOLUTION:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;Build a stream processing pipeline to batch views before writing them to a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;time series database like Cassandra&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); font-family: monospace; font-size: 0px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;&quot;&gt;%3CmxGraphModel%3E%3Croot%3E%3CmxCell%20id%3D%220%22%2F%3E%3CmxCell%20id%3D%221%22%20parent%3D%220%22%2F%3E%3CmxCell%20id%3D%222%22%20parent%3D%221%22%20style%3D%22text%3Bhtml%3D1%3BwhiteSpace%3Dwrap%3Balign%3Dleft%3BfillColor%3D%23f5f5f5%3BstrokeColor%3D%23666666%3Bspacing%3D15%3BfontSize%3D14%3BfontColor%3D%23333333%3B%22%20value%3D%22%26lt%3Bb%20style%3D&#39;font-size%3A16px%3B&#39;%26gt%3BISSUE%3A%26lt%3B%2Fb%26gt%3B%26lt%3Bbr%26gt%3BRedis%20is%20great%20for%20Likes%2C%20but%20&#39;Views&#39;%20happen%20at%20an%20exponentially%20higher%20rate.%20Writing%20every%20single%20view%20to%20a%20database%20or%20cache%20will%20still%20overwhelm%20the%20system.%20Additionally%2C%20loading%2050%20heavy%20video%20segments%20just%20to%20display%20a%2050kb%20thumbnail%20image%20on%20the%20homepage%20is%20incredibly%20inefficient.%26lt%3Bbr%26gt%3B%26lt%3Bbr%26gt%3B%26lt%3Bb%20style%3D&#39;font-size%3A16px%3B&#39;%26gt%3BSOLUTION%3A%26lt%3B%2Fb%26gt%3B%26lt%3Bbr%26gt%3BBuild%20a%20Stream%20Processing%20Pipeline%20(Apache%20Flink%20reading%20from%20Kafka)%20to%20aggregate%20and%20batch%20&#39;Views&#39;%20before%20writing%20them%20to%20a%20Time-Series%20Database%20(Cassandra).%20Also%2C%20isolate%20Thumbnails%20into%20their%20own%20optimized%20storage%20and%20CDN%20path.%22%20vertex%3D%221%22%3E%3CmxGeometry%20height%3D%22150%22%20width%3D%221090%22%20x%3D%22149%22%20y%3D%222320%22%20as%3D%22geometry%22%2F%3E%3C%2FmxCell%3E%3C%2Froot%3E%3C%2FmxGraphModel%3ESo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); font-family: monospace; font-size: 0px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;%3CmxGraphModel%3E%3Croot%3E%3CmxCell%20id%3D%220%22%2F%3E%3CmxCell%20id%3D%221%22%20parent%3D%220%22%2F%3E%3CmxCell%20id%3D%222%22%20parent%3D%221%22%20style%3D%22text%3Bhtml%3D1%3BwhiteSpace%3Dwrap%3Balign%3Dleft%3BfillColor%3D%23f5f5f5%3BstrokeColor%3D%23666666%3Bspacing%3D15%3BfontSize%3D14%3BfontColor%3D%23333333%3B%22%20value%3D%22%26lt%3Bb%20style%3D&#39;font-size%3A16px%3B&#39;%26gt%3BISSUE%3A%26lt%3B%2Fb%26gt%3B%26lt%3Bbr%26gt%3BRedis%20is%20great%20for%20Likes%2C%20but%20&#39;Views&#39;%20happen%20at%20an%20exponentially%20higher%20rate.%20Writing%20every%20single%20view%20to%20a%20database%20or%20cache%20will%20still%20overwhelm%20the%20system.%20Additionally%2C%20loading%2050%20heavy%20video%20segments%20just%20to%20display%20a%2050kb%20thumbnail%20image%20on%20the%20homepage%20is%20incredibly%20inefficient.%26lt%3Bbr%26gt%3B%26lt%3Bbr%26gt%3B%26lt%3Bb%20style%3D&#39;font-size%3A16px%3B&#39;%26gt%3BSOLUTION%3A%26lt%3B%2Fb%26gt%3B%26lt%3Bbr%26gt%3BBuild%20a%20Stream%20Processing%20Pipeline%20(Apache%20Flink%20reading%20from%20Kafka)%20to%20aggregate%20and%20batch%20&#39;Views&#39;%20before%20writing%20them%20to%20a%20Time-Series%20Database%20(Cassandra).%20Also%2C%20isolate%20Thumbnails%20into%20their%20own%20optimized%20storage%20and%20CDN%20path.%22%20vertex%3D%221%22%3E%3CmxGeometry%20height%3D%22150%22%20width%3D%221090%22%20x%3D%22149%22%20y%3D%222320%22%20as%3D%22geometry%22%2F%3E%3C%2FmxCell%3E%3C%2Froot%3E%3C%2FmxGraphModel%3E&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="237" width="897" x="255" y="2312" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="OebSlb7G5yYJ-OwYx5fL-5" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;ISSUE:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Platform is now stable, scalable and fast but it lacks personalization of videos.&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;SOLUTION:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Intoduction of a personalizated feed by using watch history and subsciptions&lt;/h1&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="179" width="982" x="151" y="3116" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="OebSlb7G5yYJ-OwYx5fL-6" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;FINAL DIAGRAM&lt;/h1&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="67" width="322" x="-186" y="3451" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="OebSlb7G5yYJ-OwYx5fL-7" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;ISSUE:&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Uploading large video files (e.g., 5GB) through the API Gateway creates performance bottlenecks, increases bandwidth consumption, and may cause server timeouts. Additionally, synchronous video processing forces users to wait for long durations, resulting in poor user experience.&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;SOLUTION:&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;To address this, the upload process should bypass the API Gateway using a Pre-Signed URL approach, allowing clients to upload directly to Object Storage. A Global CDN can be used for efficient video delivery. Video transcoding should be handled asynchronously through an Event Queue (e.g., Kafka) to ensure background processing without blocking users.&lt;/h1&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="304" width="1751" x="-278" y="562" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="OebSlb7G5yYJ-OwYx5fL-8" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;ISSUE:&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Although the video processing pipeline is optimized, viral content can generate millions of simultaneous interactions such as likes, comments, and searches. Directing all this traffic to a single SQL video database can lead to high latency, database contention, and potential system instability.&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;SOLUTION:&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;To handle this load, interactive features should be separated into independent microservices. Redis can be used for fast, in-memory like counters. A NoSQL database (such as DynamoDB) can manage high-volume comment storage. ElasticSearch can support efficient text-based search queries. WebSockets can be implemented to enable real-time updates and notifications.&lt;/h1&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="379" width="1742" x="-293" y="1389" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
